The paper deals with lower bounds for branching programs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The study of monotone Boolean functions is also a common theme in this field, which suggests cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LO (logic in computer science) as likely sub-categories. The use of exponential lower bounds also suggests cs.IT (information theory) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the study of classes of Boolean functions and their computational complexity fits well within the scope of cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
